cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: The paper addresses a manipulation problem involving a robot with a depth sensor and six degrees of freedom, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of attention focus and perception with a depth sensor suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The formulation of the problem as a Markov decision process and the use of constraints to find a good solution suggest artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as additional sub-categories. Finally, the use of a real robot in addition to simulation suggests systems and control (cs.SY) as a possible sub-category.
